2 CONT Cleopatra was of swathy, dark complexion, taking after her grandmother, a Seleucid, with some Persian blood. She had luxurious copper hair (most likely made that color by the use of henna). She reign from 51-49 B.C. and 48-30 B.C. (Foreman, Laur
2 CONC a, Cleopatra's Palace: In Search of a Legend. New York: Discovery Books, 1999).
2 CONT Cleopatra continued to hire thinkers, poets, and scientists to her court and she continued her own education as well, studying philosophy and traveling to other lands. Above all, Cleopatra was clever, intelligent, and politically oriented. She u
2 CONC nderstood and spoke Egyptian, Greek, Hebrew, Arabic, and Persian.
